A RESOLUTION
To commend Gordie White for his commitment to waterfowl conservation through Ducks
Unlimited and the preservation of North America's wetlands and wildlife.
WHEREAS, Gordie White has long recognized the critical need for organized
conservation efforts in South Louisiana; his relationship with Ducks Unlimited began in
1970, when he became one of the organization's earliest sponsors in New Iberia, Louisiana;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. White teamed up with local hunters and founded the Ducks
Unlimited New Iberia chapter in 1972; the chapter began with a vision to unite local
sportsmen and conservationists, and over the course of more than five decades, its has grown
into one of the most impactful chapters in the region; and
WHEREAS, Mr. White served as the Louisiana state chairman of Ducks Unlimited
for two years, during which he worked to advance wetland conservation initiatives
throughout Louisiana and strengthen collaborative efforts among the state's chapters; during
his tenure as state chairman, he increased the visibility of the Ducks Unlimited mission and
secured critical support for habitat restoration projects that benefit waterfowl and the
wetland ecosystem; and
WHEREAS, the New Iberia chapter has made numerous innovative contributions to
the Ducks Unlimited fundraising efforts; the chapter established "The Ducklings", a group
of dedicated female volunteers who played a vital role at fundraising events aimed at
waterfowl conservation; the original group garnered statewide recognition for its effective
fundraising strategy, which motivated other local chapters to adopt the model; and
