WHEREAS, The Ducklings concept has spread across the United States, and these
groups are now a fixture at Duck Unlimited fundraising events nationwide; and
WHEREAS, Mr. White is an established family law attorney, and he has balanced
his professional duties with his passion for conservation; he has made significant
contributions to the Ducks Unlimited cause through his ability to inspire others, build
coalitions, and move people to action; and
WHEREAS, outside of Mr. White's involvement in conservation meetings,
fundraisers, and habitat projects, he is passionate about sharing the hunting tradition with his
children and grandchildren; he holds a deeply personal connection to conservation and
believes that future generations of sportsmen deserve the opportunity to experience the
beautiful and abundant Louisiana wetlands and wildlife that have contributed to many of his
most beloved memories; and
WHEREAS, Mr. White has been married to his wife, Penny, for sixty-nine years, and
they are the proud parents of Eric T. White, Jennifer Leah White, Alexis White Delcambre,
Kathryn White Carraway, and Nicholas E. White; and
WHEREAS, Gordie White is most deserving of the highest recognition for his efforts
to grow and sustain the New Iberia chapter of Ducks Unlimited over the last half century,
and the chapter's longevity is a testament to his values of community, stewardship, and love
for the natural world.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Gordie White for his commitment to
waterfowl conservation through Ducks Unlimited and the preservation of North America's
wetlands and wildlife and does hereby extend sincere wishes that his inspiring efforts serve
to motivate younger generations of Louisianians to continue the stewardship of the state's
natural environment.
